    13‚Üí## üöÖ Quick start
    15‚Üí1.  **Create the application.**
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí    Use [degit](https://github.com/Rich-Harris/degit) to get this template.
    18‚Üí
    19‚Üí    ```shell
    20‚Üí    # Clone the template
    21‚Üí    npx degit chromaui/intro-storybook-react-template taskbox
    22‚Üí    ```
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí1.  **Install the dependencies.**
    25‚Üí
    26‚Üí    Navigate into your new site‚Äôs directory and install the necessary dependencies.
    27‚Üí
    28‚Üí    ```shell
    29‚Üí    # Navigate to the directory
    30‚Üí    cd taskbox/
    31‚Üí
    32‚Üí    # Install the dependencies
    33‚Üí    yarn
    34‚Üí    ```
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí1.  **Open the source code and start editing!**
    37‚Üí
    38‚Üí    Open the `taskbox` directory in your code editor of choice and building your first component!
    39‚Üí
    40‚Üí1.  **Browse your stories!**
    41‚Üí
    42‚Üí    Run `yarn storybook` to see your component's stories at `http://localhost:6006`
    43‚Üí
    44‚Üí## üîé What's inside?
    46‚ÜíA quick look at the top-level files and directories included with this template.
    47‚Üí
    48‚Üí    .
    49‚Üí    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .storybook
    50‚Üí    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ node_modules
    51‚Üí    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ public
    52‚Üí    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src
