    60‚Üí
    61‚Üí1.  **`.storybook`**: This directory contains Storybook's [configuration](https://storybook.js.org/docs/react/configure/overview) files.
    62‚Üí
    63‚Üí2.  **`node_modules`**: This directory contains all of the modules of code that your project depends on (npm packages).
    64‚Üí
    65‚Üí3.  **`public`**: This directory will contain the development and production build of the site.
    66‚Üí
    67‚Üí4.  **`src`**: This directory will contain all of the code related to what you will see on your application.
    68‚Üí
    69‚Üí5.  **`.gitignore`**: This file tells git which files it should not track or maintain during the development process of your project.
    70‚Üí
    71‚Üí6.  **`.index.html`**: This is the HTML page that is served when generating a development or production build.
    72‚Üí
    73‚Üí7.  **`LICENSE`**: The template is licensed under the MIT licence.
